LyuBang Zhou

About Me

I am Lyubang Zhou, a graduate student in Public Health at Peking Union Medical College.

My academic interests center on causal inference, statistical modeling for medical big data, and the application of advanced analytical tools in health policy and management.

I aim to bridge data-driven insights with evidence-based decision-making in healthcare.

Education

Peking Union Medical College (PUMC) Beijing, China

  • Master,Public Health (M.P.H.) Sept 2025 Present

Hunan University of Chinese Medicine Changsha, China

  • Bachelor,Public Affair Management Sept 2019 May 2023

Research Interests

  • Health policy evaluation (e.g., DIP, value-based payment, drug policy)
  • Medical & health big-data analytics
  • Causal inference (DiD, synthetic control, propensity score methods)
  • Statistical modeling & machine learning for healthcare

Skills

  • Programming & Analysis: Python R SAS Stata
  • Document & Workflow: LaTeX Git Quarto Markdown

Experience

Undergraduate Research Project

Innovation and Entrepreneurship Training Program for College Students (Provincial Level), Hunan Province, China Project Duration: 2021 2023

Conducted an interdisciplinary research project under the Hunan Provincial College Student Innovation and Entrepreneurship Program. Responsibilities included project design, data analysis, and report writing, focusing on management strategies and public health perspectives within the healthcare system.

To be updated

Currently engaging in research projects on statistical modeling and health policy evaluation.

Contact

Feel free to reach out via Email(Pumc.zhou@outlook.com) or explore my work on GitHub.
